aser\";s:131:\"Valentine\'s Day, also called Saint Valentine\'s Day or the Feast of Saint Valentine, is an annual holiday celebrated on February 14.\";}i:3;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-02-15\";s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"Presidents\' Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:9:\"2/15/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:63:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/presidents-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:207:\"Washington\'s Birthday is a United States federal holiday celebrated on the third Monday of February in honor of George Washington, the first President of the United States, who was born on February 22, 1732.\";}i:4;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-03-13\";s:5:\"title\";s:27:\"Daylight Saving Time starts\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:9:\"3/13/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:76:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/daylight-saving-time-starts\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:182:\"Daylight saving time (DST) is the practice of advancing clocks during summer months by one hour so that evening daylight lasts an hour longer, while sacrificing normal sunrise times.\";}i:5;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-03-27\";s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Easter Sunday\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:9:\"3/27/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:62:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/easter-sunday\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:274:\"Easter, also called Pascha (Greek/Latin) or Resurrection Sunday, is a festival and holiday celebrating the resurrection of Jesus from the dead, described in the New Testament as having occurred on the third day of his burial after his crucifixion by the Romans at Calvary c.\";}i:6;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-04-13\";s:5:\"title\";s:27:\"Thomas Jefferson\'s Birthday\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:9:\"4/13/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:75:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/thomas-jeffersons-birthday\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-05-08\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Mother\'s Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:8:\"5/8/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:60:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/mothers-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:144:\"Mother\'s Day is a celebration honoring the mother of the family, as well as motherhood, maternal bonds, and the influence of mothers in society.\";}i:8;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-05-30\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Memorial Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:9:\"5/30/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:61:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/memorial-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:135:\"Memorial Day is a federal holiday in the United States for remembering the people who died while serving in the country\'s armed forces.\";}i:9;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-06-19\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Father\'s Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:9:\"6/19/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:60:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/fathers-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:131:\"Father\'s Day is a celebration honoring fathers and celebrating fatherhood, paternal bonds, and the influence of fathers in society.\";}i:10;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-07-04\";s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"Independence Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:8:\"7/4/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:65:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/independence-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:233:\"An Independence Day is an annual event commemorating the anniversary of a nation\'s independence or statehood, usually after ceasing to be a group or part of another nation or state; more rarely after the end of a military occupation.\";}i:11;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-09-05\";s:5:\"title\";s:9:\"Labor Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:8:\"9/5/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:58:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/labor-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:95:\"Labor Day in the United States is a public holiday celebrated on the first Monday in September.\";}i:12;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-10-10\";s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Columbus Day (regional holiday)\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:10:\"10/10/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:78:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/columbus-day-regional-holiday\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:196:\"Columbus Day is a national holiday in many countries in the Americas and elsewhere which officially celebrates the anniversary of Christopher Columbus\' arrival in the Americas on October 12, 1492.\";}i:13;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-10-31\";s:5:\"title\";s:9:\"Halloween\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:10:\"10/31/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:58:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/halloween\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:256:\"Halloween or Hallowe\'en (a contraction of All Hallows\' Evening), also known as Allhalloween, All Hallows\' Eve, or All Saints\' Eve, is a celebration observed in a number of countries on 31 October, the eve of the Western Christian feast of All Hallows\' Day.\";}i:14;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-11-06\";s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"Daylight Saving Time ends\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:9:\"11/6/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:74:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/daylight-saving-time-ends\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:182:\"Daylight saving time (DST) is the practice of advancing clocks during summer months by one hour so that evening daylight lasts an hour longer, while sacrificing normal sunrise times.\";}i:15;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-11-08\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Election Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:9:\"11/8/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:61:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/election-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:63:\"Election day refers to the day when general elections are held.\";}i:16;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-11-11\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Veterans Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:10:\"11/11/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:61:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/veterans-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:185:\"Veterans Day is an official United States public holiday, observed annually on November 11, that honors military veterans; that is, persons who served in the United States Armed Forces.\";}i:17;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-11-24\";s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"Thanksgiving Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:10:\"11/24/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:65:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/thanksgiving-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:131:\"Thanksgiving Day is a national holiday celebrated in Canada, in the United States, in some of the Caribbean islands and in Liberia.\";}i:18;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-12-24\";s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Christmas Eve\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:10:\"12/24/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:62:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/christmas-eve\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:105:\"Christmas Eve is the day before Christmas Day, the festival commemorating the birth of Jesus of Nazareth.\";}i:19;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-12-25\";s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Christmas Day\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:10:\"12/25/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:62:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/christmas-day\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:265:\"Christmas or Christmas Day (Old English: Crīstesmæsse, meaning \"Christ\'s Mass\") is an annual festival commemorating the birth of Jesus Christ, observed most commonly on December 25 as a religious and cultural celebration among billions of people around the world.\";}i:20;O:18:\"thc_plugin_holiday\":5:{s:4:\"date\";s:10:\"2016-12-26\";s:5:\"title\";s:22:\"Christmas Day observed\";s:13:\"formattedDate\";s:10:\"12/26/2016\";s:3:\"url\";s:71:\"https://www.theholidaycalendar.com/united-states/christmas-day-observed\";s:6:\"teaser\";s:265:\"Christmas or Christmas Day (Old English: Crīstesmæsse, meaning \"Christ\'s Mass\") is an annual festival commemorating the birth of Jesus Christ, observed most commonly on December 25 as a religious and cultural celebration among billions of people around the world.\";}i:21;O:18:\"thc_plugin