lendar.com/maintenance-release-week-2-october-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 04 Oct 2017 15:32:37 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1358307\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:654:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the 19th Maintenance Release of 2017. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The Events Calendar 4.6.1 Events&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-2-october-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 2 October 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Courtney\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6336:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the 19th Maintenance Release of 2017. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.6.1 </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.18</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#fb\">Filter Bar 4.5.1</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ce\">Community Events 4.5.6</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed &#8220;Next Events&#8221; and &#8220;Previous Events&#8221; navigation links in list views, which would sometimes make a category-filtered list view lose its category filter as a user navigated through pages of future or past events (props @forumhelpdesk and @atomicdust for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed some layout issues with the Tribe Bar datepicker that would arise when using a Twentysixteen or Twentyfifteen child them (thanks to @stefanrueegger for reporting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevented modification of event titles within the loop when using TRIBE_MODIFY_GLOBAL_TITLE </li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed issue when exporting all-day multi-day events via iCal where the end date was one day early (Thank you @fairmont for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed issues with the jQuery Timepicker vendor script conflicting with other plugins&#8217; similar scripts (props: @hcny et al.)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed an issue that would prevent Event Aggregator scheduled imports from running</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed the &#8220;Start Time&#8221; and &#8220;End Time&#8221; timepicker fields in the event-creation screen to make it impossible to have an end date/time that comes before the start date/time</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> —  Added support within Tribe__Assets for when someone filters plugins_url() (Thank you @boonebgorges for the pull request!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Improved performance of retrieving the country and US States lists</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Limited the loading of several Tribe Common scripts and stylesheets to only load where needed within the wp-admin (props: @traildamage )</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Removed explicit width styles from app shop &#8220;buy now&#8221; buttons to better accommodate longer language strings (thanks @abrain on GitHub for submitting this fix!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Implemented a re-initializing of Select2 inputs on use of a browser&#8217;s &#8220;Back&#8221; button to prevent some UI bugs, e.g. with such inputs&#8217; placeholder attributes not being populated (props @uwefunk!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Improvement to composition of various strings, to aid translatability (props: @ramiy)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Remove unnecessary parameters from some remove_action calls in the plugin (thanks to @JPry on GitHub for submitting this fix!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Adjusted the EA cron start time so that it never gets created in the past</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Improved options format in the Event Aggregator settings</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added a filter to CSV importer for altering the delimiter, escaping, and enclosing characters</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Adjusted the <samp>tribe_update_venue()</samp> template tag so it no longer creates some unnecessary meta fields involving post_title, post_content, etc. (thanks @oheinrich for bringing this to our attention)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Improved the performance of The Events Calendar REST API tweaking some queries</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Add support for a <samp>found_posts</samp> argument in <samp>tribe_get_events</samp>, <samp>tribe_get_venues</samp> and <samp>tribe_get_organizers</samp> functions to return the number of posts found matching the current query arguments</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> — Improvements to aid translatability of text throughout plugin (props: @ramiy)</li>\n<li><strong>Deprecated</strong> — Deprecated the <samp>tribe-events-bar-date-search-default-value</samp> filter; use <samp>tribe_events_bar_date_search_default_value</samp> instead </li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ecp\">Events Calendar PRO</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> &#8211; Add link to the featured image in the Advanced List widget. New filter introduced to control this: <samp>tribe_events_list_widget_featured_image_link</samp> (props to @cabadaj007  for the feature request)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Add the possibility of importing Venue Overwrite Coordinates in Aggregator (thanks Christopher Curry for reporting)</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"fb\">Filter Bar</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed some layout issues with the &#8220;Show Filters&#8221;/&#8221;Collapse Filters&#8221; toggle button in mobile views (props to @ergosom for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Improved performance by swapping out LEFT JOINs for INNER JOINs in SQL queries</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ce\">Community Events </h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed issues with the jQuery Timepicker vendor script conflicting with other plugins&#8217; similar scripts (props: @hcny et al.)</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Event Tickets 4.5.6</li>\n<li>Event Tickets Plus 4.5.5</li>\n<li>Community Tickets 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.8</li>\n<li>Image Widget 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>\n<li>GigPress 2.3.19</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-2-october-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 2 October 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"Release: The Events Calendar – Full REST Support\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-events-calendar-full-rest-support/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 25 Sep 2017 13:31:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1353328\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:647:\"<p>Introducing the most developer-centric release we have ever done. We’ve updated The Event Calendar&#8217;s support for the REST API in version 4.6! Changelogs for The Events Calendar Ready to explore the details of this release? On to the changelogs! Fix — Added full REST support for Events, Organizers, Venues, Event Categories, and Tags &#8211; including&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-events-calendar-full-rest-support/\">Release: The Events Calendar &#8211; Full REST Support</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Courtney\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2556:\"<p>Introducing the most developer-centric release we have ever done. We’ve updated The Event Calendar&#8217;s support for the REST API in version 4.6! </p>\n<h3>Changelogs for The Events Calendar</h3>\n<p>Ready to explore the details of this release? On to the changelogs! </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Added full REST support for Events, Organizers, Venues, Event Categories, and Tags &#8211; including create, update, and delete!</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Updated Bootstrap Datepicker to v1.7.0</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added latitude/longitude to REST responses when available on venues</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added JSON-LD data to REST responses when available</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Replaced deprecated first parameter of <samp>tribe_get_organizers()</samp> with a parameter that, when specified with a truthy value, returns only organizers with upcoming events attached to them</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added linked post filters:<br />\n<samp>tribe_{$this-&gt;post_type}_has_events_excluded_post_stati</samp>, <samp>tribe_events_tribe_organizer_create</samp>, <samp>tribe_events_tribe_organizer_update</samp>, <samp>tribe_event_venue_duplicate_post_fields</samp>, <samp>tribe_event_organizer_duplicate_custom_fields</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added action: <samp>tribe_events_organizer_created</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added REST filters: <samp>tribe_rest_organizer_default_only_with_upcoming</samp>, <samp>tribe_rest_venue_default_only_with_upcoming</samp>, <samp>tribe_events_rest_term_allow_delete</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added duplicate-detection filters: <samp>tribe_duplicate_post_strategies</samp>, <samp>tribe_duplicate_post_strategy</samp>, <samp>tribe_duplicate_post_{$strategy}_strategy</samp></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Read more on getting started with full REST support at our guide: <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/introduction-events-calendar-rest-api/\">Introduction to The Events Calendar REST API</a>.</p>\n<p>Thanks for your continued support! We hope this update makes your sites much better, your jobs way easier, and your overall experience using our plugins a breeze. Cheers to you on behalf of everyone here at Modern Tribe!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-events-calendar-full-rest-support/\">Release: The Events Calendar &#8211; Full REST Support</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 18 September 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-18-september-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 20 Sep 2017 21:31:30 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1350910\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:660:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the 18th Maintenance Release of 2017. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The Events Calendar 4.5.13 Event&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-18-september-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 18 September 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Courtney\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7443:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the 18th Maintenance Release of 2017. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.13</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.5.6</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.5.5</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"“#iw&quot;\">Image Widget 4.4.6</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.13</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> — Add link to the featured image in the Events List widget. New filter introduced to control this: <samp>tribe_events_list_widget_featured_image_link</samp> (props to @cabadaj007 for the feature request)</li>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> — Remove <samp>France, Metropolitan</samp> option from country list to prevent issues with Google Maps API (thanks @varesanodotfr for pointing this out)</li>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> — Ignored Events will restore previous Status instead of setting to Publish</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Patched jQuery Resize vendor library to avoid JavaScript conflicts (props to @britner for the original report</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed a typo in the Event List widget options</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Addressed some PHP notices that would sometimes emerge in tag-filtered Post lists in the wp-admin. Thanks to @wfsec28 and others in the forums for reporting this!</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — When &#8220;Full Styles&#8221; or &#8220;Tribe Events Styles&#8221; are used, prevent duplicate featured images from showing up in the Twentyseventeen theme. Props to @want2what and others in the forums for reporting this.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Aggregator will no longer update comments while inactive</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Avoid issues when REST API archive request parameters are not in the original order (thanks @Nslaver for reporting this and providing a fix)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Aggregator prevents duplicated Records with the same params from being created</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Aggregator will now allow for some minor shifts in schedule execution time to help distribute requests to EA Service</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Improve Event Aggregator settings texts</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Add actions before and after posts are inserted or updated by Event Aggregator to allow custom functions to kick in: <samp>tribe_aggregator_before_insert_posts</samp> and <samp>tribe_aggregator_after_insert_posts</samp>, respectively.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Allow users to import CSV with Numeric named Categories by using a flag currently: <samp>%n</samp> (thanks @Shamsi for reporting)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Initialize <samp>Tribe__Deprecation</samp> on every page.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevents breakages resulting from deprecated filter hooks</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevents resetting selected Datatables rows when changing pages (thanks @templesinai for reporting)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added an id attribute to dropdowns generated by the Fields API</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.5.6</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Prevent occasional issue with email content-type not being reset after ticket emails were sent. Props to @jappleton in the forums for reporting this!</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Hide unused Back button when moving Tickets to another post</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevent multiple instances of the &#8220;View your RSVPs and Tickets&#8221; link from showing on single events (or other ticket-enabled post types). Props to @svkg in the forums for reporting this.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Clear attendee cache when a ticket gets moved to another post</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Open the exportable CSV file of Attendees in a new tab to accommodate Google Chrome&#8217;s strict handling of file and MIME types, preventing some console errors and notices in Chrome.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Added &#8220;View Tickets&#8221; link to Custom Post Types when appropriate. Thank you @19ideas for helping identify this</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fix some layout issues with the &#8220;Email Attendees&#8221; modal in the Attendees list admin view, especially when viewed on phones or tablets. Props to @event-control for reporting this!</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Avoid notice-level errors when calling ticket stock functions in relation to events with unlimited stock (props to Lou Anne for highlighting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Documented filter for available Ticket Modules, and used its method instead more places</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Initialize <samp>Tribe__Deprecation</samp> on every page.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevents breakages resulting from deprecated filter hooks</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevents resetting selected Datatables rows when changing pages (thanks @templesinai for reporting)</li>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> — Remove <samp>France, Metropolitan</samp> option from country list to prevent issues with Google Maps API (thanks @varesanodotfr for pointing this out)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added an id attribute to dropdowns generated by the Fields API</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.5.5</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fix issue where &#8220;Who&#8217;s Attending?&#8221; list would often incorrectly report the number of people attending an event.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevent blank option values for fields like radio, checkbox, and dropdown.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Make the bottom-border on some WooCommerce ticket elements more consistent in color and width. Props to @webidextrous for reporting this!</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"“eb”\">Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.8</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Adjustments to support Eventbrite packages</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"“iw”\">Image Widget</h3>\n<p>Image Widget 4.4.6 shipped on 12 September 2017.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>New</strong> — Added new filter <samp>tribe_image_widget_instance_description</samp> for more control over how the description field is handled.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevent broken HTML in the &#8220;description&#8221; field that sometimes arose with certain user roles. Props to users @bridgetashley and @JoshRoy spotting this one!</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Events Calendar PRO</li>\n<li>Filter Bar</li>\n<li>Community Events</li>\n<li>Community Tickets</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus</li>\n<li>GigPress</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-18-september-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 18 September 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"Hotfix – The Events Calendar 4.5.12.3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-the-events-calendar-4-5-12-3/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 20 Sep 2017 02:37:37 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1351611\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:624:\"<p>We&#8217;re pleased to announce that The Events Calendar 4.5.12.3 is now available, which resolves an issue related to the display of events in the default Month View. This issue was introduced with WordPress version 4.8.2 and impacts all previous versions of The Events Calendar&#8211;all users are encouraged to update as soon as possible. No other changes&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-the-events-calendar-4-5-12-3/\">Hotfix – The Events Calendar 4.5.12.3</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Caroline\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1156:\"<p>We&#8217;re pleased to announce that <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/the-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Events Calendar 4.5.12.3</a> is now available, which resolves an issue related to the display of events in the default Month View. This issue was introduced with WordPress version 4.8.2 and impacts all previous versions of The Events Calendar&#8211;<strong>all users are encouraged to update as soon as possible.</strong> No other changes were made to any other areas of the plugin, and we apologize to anyone who might have been affected by this issue.</p>\n<p>Thank you to all of our users who took the time to bring this issue to our attention! If you should have any other questions or concerns, please don&#8217;t hesitate to reach out to us over on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support-forums/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">our support forums</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-the-events-calendar-4-5-12-3/\">Hotfix – The Events Calendar 4.5.12.3</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"Nonprofit Spotlight: Creative Animal Foundation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/nonprofit-spotlight-creative-animal-foundation/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 18 Sep 2017 22:25:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Nonprofit Spotlight\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1350061\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:645:\"<p>For the past five years, Modern Tribe has been proud to lend support to the WordPress and nonprofit communities through our Nonprofit Partnership Program. This program provides free licensing for Events Calendar PRO or Event Tickets Plus to qualifying nonprofits, allowing organizations ready access to premium tools that make it easier to promote their events,&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/nonprofit-spotlight-creative-animal-foundation/\">Nonprofit Spotlight: Creative Animal Foundation</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Caroline\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7426:\"<p>For the past five years, Modern Tribe has been proud to lend support to the WordPress and nonprofit communities through our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/do-you-offer-discounts-for-nonprofit-organizations/\">Nonprofit Partnership Program</a>. This program provides free licensing for <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/\">Events Calendar PRO</a> or <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets-plus/\">Event Tickets Plus</a> to qualifying nonprofits, allowing organizations ready access to premium tools that make it easier to promote their events, generate revenue for charitable causes, and otherwise do good work.</p>\n<p>Our program has undergone a number of changes in the half-decade since its inception, and in that time, we&#8217;ve received applications from thousands of nonprofit organizations interested in working with our products. We couldn&#8217;t be more thrilled to see the many ways that these organizations are benefitting from the use of our plugins.</p>\n<p>In the interest of further promoting the incredible efforts of our nonprofit partners, we&#8217;re happy to introduce the <strong>Nonprofit Spotlight</strong> as a new recurring fixture here on TheEventsCalendar.com. Each entry will serve to highlight one of our accepted nonprofits and showcase the unique ways in which our products are being used. We hope that you&#8217;ll enjoy learning more about these great organizations! <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<hr />\n<h3><a href=\"http://creativeanimal.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Creative Animal Foundation</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://creativeanimal.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1350075\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Web-Header-Logo-650color.png\" alt=\"Creative Animal Foundation logo\" width=\"650\" height=\"144\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Web-Header-Logo-650color.png 650w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Web-Header-Logo-650color-140x31.png 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Web-Header-Logo-650color-300x66.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Web-Header-Logo-650color-430x95.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Web-Header-Logo-650color-645x143.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Web-Header-Logo-650color-460x102.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Web-Header-Logo-650color-600x133.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Web-Header-Logo-650color-500x111.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" /></a></p>\n<p>When advocating for wildlife conservation and sustainable living is your aim, sometimes it pays to think small. The brainchild of wildlife educators Stephanie Arne and Tim Davison, <a href=\"http://www.creativeanimal.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Creative Animal Foundation</a> is a 501(c)3 organization dedicated to promoting global conservation and the protection of animal species, natural habitats, and our oceans and waterways. The embodiment of their nonprofit&#8217;s mission and their passion for sustainability comes in the form of Arne and Davison&#8217;s spectacular tiny home on wheels&#8211;a traveling installation of sorts that&#8217;s equal parts home, office, studio, and museum exhibit.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1350065\" style=\"width: 675px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-1350065\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-665x374.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"665\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-665x374.jpg 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-140x79.jpg 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-300x169.jpg 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-768x431.jpg 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-430x242.jpg 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-645x362.jpg 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-1068x600.jpg 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-460x258.jpg 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-600x337.jpg 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest-500x281.jpg 500w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/Tiny-Line-Jax-Green-Lion-Fest.jpg 1344w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Source: Creative Animal Foundation</p></div>\n<p>To date, Arne and Davison have invited over 15,000 people from all walks of life into their home, sparking conversations and opening minds to new possibilities in the realm of low-impact, environmentally-conscious living. And with at least 50 stops planned for their 2017 tour, there&#8217;s still ample opportunity to join in on the fun! Visitors can see past destinations, check out upcoming tour dates, and even suggest next stops from the <a href=\"http://www.creativeanimal.org/tour/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Creative Animal Tour</a> page.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1350071\" style=\"width: 380px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://www.creativeanimal.org/tour/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1350071\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/caf_tour_page.png\" alt=\"Creative Animal Foundation tour page\" width=\"370\" height=\"516\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/caf_tour_page.png 370w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/caf_tour_page-61x85.png 61w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/caf_tour_page-215x300.png 215w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 370px) 100vw, 370px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Source: Creative Animal Foundation</p></div>\n<p>A custom implementation of Events Calendar PRO blends beautifully with the site&#8217;s theme, and we&#8217;re loving the use of PRO&#8217;s shortcode functionality to nest a full calendar view comfortably amid other page elements. This is a great example of how Events Calendar PRO can integrate seamlessly into existing site content&#8211;a simple setup is all that&#8217;s needed to produce a terrific result!</p>\n<p>There&#8217;s plenty more great content to enjoy over on the foundation&#8217;s website, including video tours, regular blog updates, and even an online shop. Head on over to <a href=\"http://www.creativeanimal.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">creativeanimal.org</a> to see the rest of it, and don&#8217;t forget to check out the Creative Animal Tour when they&#8217;re in your neck of the woods!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/nonprofit-spotlight-creative-animal-foundation/\">Nonprofit Spotlight: Creative Animal Foundation</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"The Events Calendar 4.5.12.2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-4-5-12-2/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 08 Sep 2017 18:20:39 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1346803\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:596:\"<p>We are pleased to announce the immediate availability of The Events Calendar 4.5.12.2, which resolves an issue impacting some Event Aggregator users whereby scheduled imports would not run manually, under some circumstances. This follows hot on the heels of our 4.5.12 and 4.5.12.1 releases and is part of our drive to improve the overall experience&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-4-5-12-2/\">The Events Calendar 4.5.12.2</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Barry\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1156:\"<p>We are pleased to announce the immediate availability of <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/the-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\">The Events Calendar 4.5.12.2</a>, which resolves an issue impacting some Event Aggregator users whereby scheduled imports would not run manually, under some circumstances. </p>\n<p>This follows hot on the heels of our 4.5.12 and 4.5.12.1 releases and is part of our drive to improve the overall experience for users of our Event Aggregator service: no other changes were made to any other areas of the plugin.</p>\n<p>Automated updates should be available immediately: should you have any questions, please don&#8217;t hesitate to reach out to the team on the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support-forums/\" target=\"_blank\">on the forums</a> <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-4-5-12-2/\">The Events Calendar 4.5.12.2</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"The Events Calendar 4.5.12.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-4-5-12-1/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 07 Sep 2017 13:39:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1345920\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:588:\"<p>We are pleased to announce the immediate availability of The Events Calendar 4.5.12.1, which resolves an issue impacting some Event Aggregator users whereby imported events could inadvertently be duplicated. No other changes were made to any other areas of the plugin and we apologize to anyone who might have been affected by this issue. If&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-4-5-12-1/\">The Events Calendar 4.5.12.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Barry\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2755:\"<p>We are pleased to announce the immediate availability of <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/the-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\">The Events Calendar 4.5.12.1</a>, which resolves an issue impacting some Event Aggregator users whereby imported events could inadvertently be duplicated. </p>\n<p>No other changes were made to any other areas of the plugin and we apologize to anyone who might have been affected by this issue. If you <em>were</em> impacted, we would recommend downloading the following plugin to help clean things up:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/remove-duplicate-imported-events.zip\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f50c.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Remove Duplicate Imported Events</a></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s in the regular plugin zip format, so simply visit the plugin admin screen, click Add New then upload and activate it. It may take a while for it to complete cleanup (or it may be near instant, depending on how much work it needs to do) and you&#8217;ll know when it&#8217;s finished because an admin notice will appear telling you as much:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"939\" height=\"63\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-1345923\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete.png 939w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete-140x9.png 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete-300x20.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete-768x52.png 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete-665x45.png 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete-430x29.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete-645x43.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete-460x31.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete-600x40.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/09/cleanup-complete-500x34.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 939px) 100vw, 939px\" /></p>\n<p>Thank you for your patience and support while we worked on this. As ever, please don&#8217;t hesitate to reach out to us <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support-forums/\" target=\"_blank\">on the forums</a> should you have any questions.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-4-5-12-1/\">The Events Calendar 4.5.12.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 4 September 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-4-september-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 06 Sep 2017 18:39:53 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1345251\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:658:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the seventeenth Maintenance Release of 2017. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The Events Calendar 4.5.12&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-4-september-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 4 September 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Victor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8408:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the seventeenth Maintenance Release of 2017. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.12</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.17</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.5.5</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.5.4</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.12</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issue where, with certain date formats chosen in the Events display settings, the &#8220;Next Month&#8221; link navigation wasn&#8217;t working (props to @tttammi and others for reporting this issue!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed a typo in REST API Swagger documentation that mentioned &#8220;organizer&#8221; when it should have stated &#8220;venue&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issues with Event Aggregator queueing system where events might be duplicated or incorrectly updated</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Prevent notice when the Aggregator Record title is an array</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Allows Aggregator Google Map settings to extend the Global Setting by default (props to queerio for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Prevent Warnings when throwing WordPress admin notices from Aggregator daily usage limit (props to cigarplanner for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Resolved problem where Aggregator wouldn&#8217;t allow you to remove filtering terms for Records</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Allow any datepicker format to be used on Aggregator filtering Events (props to matthewseymour for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Added check to see if log directory is readable before listing logs within it (thank you @rodrigochallengeday-org and @richmondmom for reporting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added method into Date Utils class to allow us to easily convert all datepicker formats into the default one</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added a filter to customize the list of states in the USA that are available to drop-downs when creating or editing venues</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Datatables Head and Foot checkboxes will not select all items, only the current page</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Included tooltip for Aggregator &#8220;Hide &amp; Ignore&#8221; button for events</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added all the Aggregator Origins to the Admin Bar</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filters: <samp>tribe_get_state_options</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added template tags: <samp>maybe_format_from_datepicker()</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 2 new strings added, 90 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 1 obsoleted</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> (Common) &#8211; 3 new strings added, 46 updated, 1 fuzzied, and 4 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.17</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Meta building for Recurrence has a few more conditionals to prevent Fatals</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Setup postdata in Week view so that the default template tags can be used in theme overrides (thank you ThemeFusion for recommending this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Resolved issue where the warning for tickets on recurring events sometimes failed to display</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; A hidden input that detects if the event is recurring</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Changed views: <samp>pro/week/single-event.php</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 1 new strings added, 31 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.5.5</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue where RSVP options would often fail to show up on custom post types (thanks to tvtap for reporting this issue!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Confirm RSVP button not showing when last ticket was out of stock</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue where email address links were getting http:// prepended in the RSVP list (thank you to @petemorelli for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Resolved issue where tribe_events_count_available_tickets() sometimes returned the wrong stock count (props to Florian for reporting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Added check to see if log directory is readable before listing logs within it (thank you @rodrigochallengeday-org and @richmondmom for reporting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; RSVP non attendance email filters names are now unique (thanks to solwebsolutions for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Include full event start and end date in Tickets Email (thank you @pagan11460 for the suggestion!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Improve performance of the addition of the &#8220;Attendees&#8221; row action link in wp-admin list tables (props to pixeldesigns for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Changed views: <samp>tickets/email.php</samp>, <samp>tickets/orders-link.php</samp>, <samp>tickets/orders-rsvp.php</samp>, and <samp>tickets/rsvp.php</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filters: <samp>tribe_events_set_notice</samp>, <samp>tribe_rsvp_non_attendance_email_headers</samp>, <samp>tribe_rsvp_non_attendance_email_attachments</samp>, <samp>tribe_rsvp_non_attendance_email_recipient</samp>, <samp>tribe_rsvp_non_attendance_email_subject</samp>, and <samp>tribe_rsvp_non_attendance_email_content</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filters: <samp>tribe_event_tickets_plus_email_meta_fields</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added actions: <samp>tribe_tickets_before_front_end_ticket_form</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 53 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> (Common) &#8211; 3 new strings added, 46 updated, 1 fuzzied, and 4 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.5.4</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue where &#8220;Who&#8217;s Attending?&#8221; list would often fail to show up on custom post types</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed dates in Orders report for items with status other than complete</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Ensure that if an Attendee is deleted, it cannot be &#8220;checked in&#8221; (props to ahelman for reporting this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added new filter <samp>tribe_event_tickets_plus_email_meta_fields</samp> (thanks @carlosmachado for the suggestion)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Adjusted multiline option markup for meta fields type text</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Fixed incorrect plugin version in code documentation</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Purge unused meta fields template file</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Changed views: <samp>eddtickets/tickets.php</samp> and <samp>wootickets/tickets.php</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; New template tags: <samp>unhook_event_tickets_order_link_logic()</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 1 new strings added, 19 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Filter Bar 4.5</li>\n<li>Community Events 4.5.5</li>\n<li>Community Tickets 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.7.1</li>\n<li>Image Widget 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>\n<li>GigPress 2.3.19</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-4-september-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 4 September 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"The Events Calendar &amp; WordPress 4.4+\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-wordpress-4-4/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 30 Aug 2017 01:47:22 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1333196\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:632:\"<p>If you&#8217;ve been keeping up with our blog posts of late, you may have noticed an extra addition to our notes for last week&#8217;s maintenance release: WordPress 4.5 is now the minimum officially supported WordPress version for The Events Calendar, Events Calendar PRO, Event Tickets, Community Events, and GigPress. A minimum WordPress version of 4.4 or higher&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-wordpress-4-4/\">The Events Calendar &#038; WordPress 4.4+</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Caroline\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5988:\"<p>If you&#8217;ve been keeping up with our blog posts of late, you may have noticed an extra addition to our notes for <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-21-august-2017/\">last week&#8217;s maintenance release</a>: <strong>WordPress 4.5 is now the minimum officially supported WordPress version </strong>for <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar/\">The Events Calendar</a>, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/\">Events Calendar PRO</a>, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets</a>, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/\">Community Events</a>, and <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/gigpress/\">GigPress</a>. A minimum WordPress version of 4.4 or higher is now required for <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-filterbar/\">Filter Bar</a>, as well.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll see this change being applied to our other free and premium plugins in the coming weeks.</p>\n<h3>Why the Change?</h3>\n<p>For quite some time now, we&#8217;ve supported older versions of WordPress dating as far back as version 3.9, which was originally released in April of 2014. In software development terms, three years represents a <em>considerable</em> span of time, and we&#8217;ve seen quite a few significant releases from the WordPress community since! Adjusting our expectations for a minimum supported version of WordPress comes with a number of benefits for not just our development team, but for our user community as a whole.</p>\n<h4>Greater Stability</h4>\n<p>Keeping your site current with recent WordPress updates will provide you with access to important fixes and security improvements from the open-source WordPress community. These changes help to keep your site running smoothly and afford extra protection from hacks and exploits, so they&#8217;re definitely worth considering for all users.</p>\n<h4>Improved Compatibility</h4>\n<p>Moving to a minimum supported WordPress version of 4.5 keeps The Events Calendar and its related plugins in step with other popular plugin offerings, such as WooCommerce (which carries a minimum requirement of version 4.4) and Jetpack (which requires at least WordPress 4.7).</p>\n<p>Keeping your WordPress install up to date ensures that you&#8217;ll have access to the latest and greatest versions of all of these plugins as they become available. And while compatibility between plugins isn&#8217;t always a sure thing, you&#8217;re more likely to have a smooth experience with plugins targeted for the same or similar WordPress versions.</p>\n<h4>Sharpened Support</h4>\n<p>Reducing the number of versions that we support allows us to better target our efforts when users report issues in our forums. By moving to a more recent version of WordPress, you&#8217;ll be joining the largest portion of our user base on a more stable platform &#8211; and you&#8217;ll reap the benefits in the form of better, more focused support from our team.</p>\n<h4>Resource Efficiency</h4>\n<p>Focusing our development efforts towards more recent versions of WordPress frees up development and QA resources that would otherwise be spent ensuring broad compatibility with outdated software. This means that more of our efforts can be applied to improvements that matter to <em>you</em>, like bug fixes and feature additions.</p>\n<h4>Who’s Affected?</h4>\n<p>If you&#8217;re already running our plugins on a WordPress version of 4.5 or newer, you can rest easy regarding these changes. Users of current WordPress architectures who are moving to the latest versions of our plugins shouldn&#8217;t notice any differences in our update or installation processes.</p>\n<p>Any users remaining on older WordPress platforms will see an incompatibility notice when attempting to install the latest version of The Events Calendar, Event Tickets, or GigPress from the WordPress plugin directory.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1338864\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated.png\" alt=\"Notice that displays when attempting to install The Events Calendar on an older unsupported version of WordPress\" width=\"533\" height=\"261\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated.png 533w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-140x69.png 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-300x147.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-430x211.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-460x225.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-500x245.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 533px) 100vw, 533px\" /></p>\n<p>Versions of our plugins that require WordPress 4.4 or above can still generally be installed on earlier versions of WordPress. However, please be aware that problems may result that our support team would be unable to assist with.</p>\n<p>We hope this post helps to clarify our thinking in reaching this decision. We truly believe this move represents a positive step forward for our continued development efforts as well as the needs of our user base.</p>\n<p>With these changes in place, we&#8217;ll be better equipped to focus our efforts where they count: on crafting solid code and implementing great new features to make your projects even better.</p>\n<p>On behalf of all of us on the team, thanks so much for your continued support!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-wordpress-4-4/\">The Events Calendar &#038; WordPress 4.4+</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 21 August 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-21-august-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 24 Aug 2017 21:58:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1338531\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:652:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the sixteenth Maintenance Release of 2017. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The Events Calendar 4.5.11&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-21-august-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 21 August 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Victor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8413:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the sixteenth Maintenance Release of 2017. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.11</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.16</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.5.4</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ce\">Community Events 4.5.5</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#gp\">GigPress 2.3.19</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.11</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Avoid Event Aggregator previews or scheduled imports being marked as failures</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed start and end date limit parsing for events archive in the REST API code</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue with <samp>tribe_events_get_the_excerpt()</samp> returning a read more link that sometimes pointed to the current page</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed Post ID not being sent to the_title filter for Organizers and Venues (props Anna L.)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue where Month View tooltips would often go off-screen in some smaller viewport sizes</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issue that would sometimes render Event Aggregator options invalid even with a valid license</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issue where the mobile.php template file would often fail to include an event&#8217;s featured image</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Resolved issue where invalid linked post IDs prevent proper updates on linked posts (props to Mathew L. and a few others for highlighting this issue)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Do not hijack the blog when the main events page is configured to appear on the site&#8217;s homepage (our thanks to Jason and others for flagging this problem)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; remove extra trailing double-quotes at the end of the timepicker data-format attributes</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issues where Event Aggregator scheduled imports could not run other than manually</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Ensure valid license keys save as expected</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removing WP Plugin API result adjustments</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevent stray commas from showing up for some event venues in the List View</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevent stray commas from showing up for some event venues in the Day View</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Modify certain event queries to widen the window of opportunity for query caching (props @garretjohnson)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Improve Event Aggregator message regarding Facebook token expiration</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Support importing from URLs (Event Aggregator) where the protocol hasn&#8217;t been specified by defaulting to HTTP</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed WP API adjustments</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter: <samp>tribe_aggregator_meta_source</samp> to filter the Event Aggregator import source</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter: <samp>tribe_events_linked_post_meta_values_{$current_linked_post_meta_key}</samp> for filtering the array of values retrieved for a specific linked post meta field</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Updated views: <samp>src/views/day/single-event.php</samp> and <samp>src/views/list/single-event.php</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.5</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; Improvements to various strings to improve ease of translation (props to @ramiy)</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 5 new strings added, 56 updated, 1 fuzzied, and 3 obsoleted [the-events-calendar]</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.16</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> &#8211; Added ability to filter events by location through WP_Query arguments <samp>tribe_geoloc</samp>, <samp>tribe_geoloc_lat</samp>, and <samp>tribe_geoloc_lng</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Restored functionality to Map View and location search, which were both failing under certain circumstances with certain venues</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Lock down the low-risk queries for posterity in Tribe__Events__Pro__Geo_Loc with $wpdb->prepare</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Recurrence bug with updating weekly rules, used w date format instead of N</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Enqueue the Minical Widget&#8217;s stylesheet and scripts in the <samp>&#x3C;head&#x3E;</samp> when possible</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Added default highlight color for featured events in the Advanced List Widget (thank you @jhoughton1 and @solel for reporting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed translation issue with custom fields label on event editor page</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Improve accuracy of &#8220;Next Events&#8221; link on single-venue pages, so that it only shows when there are truly more events to see</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue where the Google Maps script and its Geolocation script would load on events archive views (other than Map View) even when the &#8220;Hide location search&#8221; option was checked (thanks to Teresa A.)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added per-event CSS class in Week view, it indexes how many events start at the same time allowing unique CSS for each</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; New hook: <samp>tribe_geoloc_pre_get_venues_in_geofence</samp> for circumventing get_venues_in_geofence database query</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; New hooks: <samp>tribe_events_single_venue_posts_per_page</samp> and <samp>tribe_venue_upcoming_events</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Updated views: <samp>src/views/pro/list/venue-nav.php</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.5</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 6 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted [tribe-events-calendar-pro]</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.5.4</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed WP API adjustments</li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.5</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 18 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted [event-tickets]</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ce\">Community Events 4.5.5</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Set the Show Map and Show Map Link fields to true by default, restoring the behavior from past versions</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Fixed some typos that would sometimes show up in the Organizer selection fields</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter: <samp>tribe_events_community_apply_map_defaults</samp> for filtering venue map fields</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 28 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted [tribe-events-community]</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"gp\">GigPress 2.3.19</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter <samp>gigpress_related_post_types</samp> to allow more than just &#8220;post&#8221; for related posts</li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.5</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Filter Bar 4.5</li>\n<li>Event Tickets Plus 4.5.3</li>\n<li>Community Tickets 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.7.1</li>\n<li>Image Widget 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-21-august-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 21 August 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:35:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:10:{s:6:\"server\";s:5:\"nginx\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Wed, 11 Oct 2017 19:25:37 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:12:\"x-powered-by\";s:23:\"PHP/5.6.29-1~dotdeb+7.1\";s:4:\"vary\";s:6:\"Cookie\";s:4:\"etag\";s:34:\"\"3b2dc5efb7afda7ee2a870063a1010e7\"\";s:12:\"x-robots-tag\";s:15:\"noindex, follow\";s:4:\"link\";s:66:\"<https://theeventscalendar.com/wp-json/>; rel=\"https://api.w.org/\"\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Wed, 11 Oct 2017 18:39:50 GMT\";s:13:\"cache-control\";s:29:\"max-age=3600, must-revalidate\";}}s:5:\"build\";s:14:\"20130911040210\";}','no'),(933,'_transient_timeout_feed_mod_0d102f2a1f4d6bc90eb8c6ffe18e56ed','1507793137','no'),(934,'_transient_feed_mod_0d102f2a1f4d6bc90eb8c6ffe18e56ed','1507749937','no'),(935,'_site_transient_timeout_community-events-1aecf33ab8525ff212ebdffbb438372e','150779